agp*|hrt|ffs|mtf*|*siss*

>>29089583
There are two versions. The first is silicone implants, which looks bad. Basically you'll have exaggerated mommy hips with skinny chicken legs. The second is a fat transfer, which is lipo on your stomach, and then pumping the fat back into your butt, hips, and thighs, which is what the girl in OP had. It'll look (comparatively) good, but it starts wearing off after a year or two. It also presupposes that you have enough fat to transfer, and that you don't lose weight afterward, because odds are your new hips will be the first to go. Once a fat cell reaches the end of its lifespan it'll be recycled and new fat will grow at a lipocyte, which on a woman (or a tranny who's been on HRT for a few years) means boobs, butt, or thighs, and on a man mostly means belly. Since the fat transfer doesn't move any lipocytes, as fat is recycled the effect of the transfer diminishes.

Worth bearing in mind that a lot of clinics doing this sort of thing have a very poor track record for hygiene. Make sure you go to someone who knows what they're doing, so you don't end up like the women who go to Turkey for a butt lift and come home in caskets because the "clinic" gave them medieval-level sepsis.

>QOTT
No human bodies but growing up around rodents my whole life (especially mice) i've seen countless mouse, rat, hamster, gerbil, and asf bodies as well as one guinea pig body. Usually they're in their beds curled up asleep, stiff and cold. My mother and I would wrap them up in paper towels, put them in ziploc bags, and put them in the freezer for a bit. We'd throw most of them out after freezing, but we'd bury some that were especially close to us.
The worst, though, were the ones that died of cancer or were coated in tumors when they died. Most that died like this were the ASFS that we paired our boys with. Female rats also get horrible tumors, but we never really got any for that reason. Sometimes the poor girls would be entirely coated in red, painful tumors for up to weeks before their deaths. I always felt so awful for them. Some die in other terrible ways. One boy bled to death because he ripped his own limbs off, starting with his ears and then his balls. Sometimes baby mice are eaten. Sometimes they're failure to thrive. Sometimes they get Waltzing Mouse Syndrome that's bad enough they can't eat, sleep or drink. Sometimes they're brindles and get obscenely obese. It's a very sad time owning rodents. I don't own mice anymore, it made me too sad too often.

Teamwork Edition
previous: >>29075785

Goal of the thread: Work on one skill you wish to be better at. It can be as simple as reading a small paragraph of a text book on the subject.
Daily goals can be repeated. Remember to keep score, it can only go up!

>What is this thread for?
Getting better is hard, and sucks. A lot. It does not get easier doing it alone.
Share resources and experiences with combating depression, anxiety, personal issues, achieving or maintaining a healthy weight, etc.
>Why is this thread /lgbt/?
Struggles with mental and physical health are an indisputable part of /lgbt/ life, be it from dysphoria, social pressure, heartbreak, or just unfortunate lifestyle choices.
>Notes to consider:
Please be civil. Shame is your greatest enemy in fighting urges of self abuse (be it sh, drugs, or just self deprecation). Relapsing into bad and unhealthy habits is to be expected, the goal is to increase the average amount of time it takes between relapses. Any improvement is a victory no matter how small. Your worth and right to get better are non-negotiable. And most importantly:
WE ARE NOT THERAPISTS, WE DON'T REPLACE MEDICATION
>Note on advice
Generic advice won't necessarily help you in particular, but for those it does it is an essential foundation to build future progress on, not a miracle cure. Do not underestimate the effects subtle changes to your lifestyle can have. Try first, keep us posted on your progress, build from there.

We are *always* short on self help resources, so if anything was useful to you, let us know!
Since the OP is getting too long I moved all resources into their own post, see below!

most things like this are made in yeast or e.coli. because of things like penicillin, which is made by bacteria, there are very advanced technologies to culture these bacteria. They have big vats which are filled with basically sugar and water and protien and everything the bacteria needs to live, and they are kept at the perfect temperature, and stirred at the perfect rate with special blades, and all the conditions are perfect for that bacteria.
>find gene sequence that encodes for a protien that makes the molecule you want
>pull out yeast's dna
>splice in your sequence
>put yeast's dna back in
>make that yeast divide a bunch
>now you have a bunch of estrogen
>kill all the yeast and use a bunch of various reactions that dissolves everything but the estrogen
>clean up the estrogen and combine it with binders and fillers (basically chalk and gum, to make it stick together as a pill)
>press it into pills
they only use another source if there is already a very efficient pathway. for instance, if a plant grows a molecule that is very close to your target mollecule, and you can't find a way to make your target molecule using a protien (so you can't encode it into the yeast genome), then you just farm a bunch of the plant and extract from there.
as to why plants have estrogens: most of them are believed to be for population control of herbivorous animals. Exogenous estrogen lowers fertility in female animals (specifically it mimics the period after birth so the body knows to not become fertile for a bit to allow itself to recover).
So if a grass or bean or whatever has a bunch of estrogen in it, (which would be targeted to a specific animal btw. different animals use different molecules as estrogens) then if that animal eats too much of the plant, it wont be fertile and over time that influences the animal population to only eat that plant sparingly.
All of this is just a theory btw, but its the current best theory.
